S., Nedoroscik scored a 14.866 to clinch Team USA's place on the podium.\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.7889000775399896, \"rank\": 0.2675827915745614, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterward, Nedoroscik, the 2021 world pommel horse champion, participated in a cathartic celebration with his U.S. teammates.\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was just the greatest moment of my life,\\\" Nedoroscik said after the event,according to USA Today.\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\", \"score\": 0.9999999974138518, \"rank\": 2.5860795383826616e-09, \"text\": \"USA Today\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Today\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nedoroscik, 25, is a first-time Olympian who made the U.S. men's gymnastics team as a single-event specialist.\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 723, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 645, \"end\": 653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999708734326, \"rank\": 2.912665733801919e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999640420172349, \"rank\": 2.9860562624237766e-05, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will compete in the made the U.S. men's gymnastics team as a single-event specialist.\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999640420172349, \"rank\": 2.9860562624237766e-05, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will compete in the individual finals later this week but first faced a pressurized spot.\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 905, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nedoroscik's pommel horse routine would determine whether Team USA won a medal, and he nailed it.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.7889000775399896, \"rank\": 0.2675827915745614, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI knew he had it as soon as I saw him take the podium and do his arm swings and take his warmup,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Penn State men's gymnastics coach Randy Jepson said in a statement.\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1108, \"end\": 1118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\", \"score\": 0.742852458188063, \"rank\": 0.34464642494657466, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just all about the first circle he does and as soon as he got that I knew his tempo was right and he was off to the races.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1308, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t be happier for Penn State\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s second bronze medalist at the Olympics.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Stephen Nedoroscik had to score big on pommel horse for Team USA in the last rotation\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6AND HE DID.\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1337, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_Quakers_football\", \"score\": 0.9692781179347365, \"rank\": 0.025276339017923487, \"text\": \"Penn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_Quakers_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_Quakers_football\"}, {\"begin\": 1396, \"end\": 1414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Nedoroscik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\"}, {\"begin\": 1452, \"end\": 1460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.7889000775399896, \"rank\": 0.2675827915745614, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a4\\u00af\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00ba: NBC and Peacockpic.twitter.com/hkhiHpovyh  Nedoroscik, who graduated from Penn State with a degree in electrical engineering, competed for the Nittany Lions from 2016-2020.\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.999999991590812, \"rank\": 8.237550416656917e-09, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1580, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\", \"score\": 0.742852458188063, \"rank\": 0.34464642494657466, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\"}, {\"begin\": 1649, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\", \"score\": 0.9999995795725201, \"rank\": 3.776234248334097e-07, \"text\": \"Nittany Lions\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was a two-time NCAA champion on the pommel horse in 2017-18 and was a four-time All-American.\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1697, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999994934215839, \"rank\": 5.040591531866046e-07, \"text\": \"NCAA champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2020, Nedoroscik became the first specialist to win the Nissen-Emery Award as the nation\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s top senior gymnast.\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was pursuing his third NCAA title on pommel horse when the championships were canceled.\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1918, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999660184565458, \"rank\": 3.39815487936728e-05, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"